ry.ts:\n  Line 542:  * Find the most relevant spec folders for a given query using\n\n  Line 1190:  * Discover the most relevant spec folder for a query.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts:\n  Line 5: // P(relevant) using a monotonic calibration model fit from labeled\n\n  Line 26:  * `relevant` is the binary ground-truth label (1 = relevant, 0 = not).\n\n  Line 31:   relevant: 0 | 1;\n\n  Line 43:   relevant: 0 | 1;\n\n  Line 48:  * (rawValue) with non-decreasing `y` (P(relevant)); applyCalibration\n\n  Line 75:     throw new Error('labeled set must be a JSON array of {query, memoryId, relevant}');\n\n  Line 84:     const relevant = e.relevant;\n\n  Line 91:     if (relevant !== 0 && relevant !== 1) {\n\n  Line 92:       throw new Error(`labeled set entry ${i} relevant must be 0 or 1`);\n\n  Line 94:     return { query, memoryId, relevant };\n\n  Line 138:  * P(relevant) and is guaranteed non-decreasing, so a higher raw confidence\n\n  Line 147:     .filter((s) => Number.isFinite(s.rawValue) && (s.relevant === 0 || s.relevant === 1))\n\n  Line 148:     .map((s) => ({ x: clamp01(s.rawValue), y: s.relevant as number }))\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/folder-relevance.ts:\n  Line 196:  * This narrows the result set to the most relevant spec folders,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/channel-representation.ts:\n  Line 10:  * The 0.005 floor prevents promoting genuinely irrelevant results while remaining\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:\n  Line 615:  * so confidence.value approximates P(relevant). Opt-in (default OFF): the only\n\n  Line 650:  * exclusion is redundant and hides legitimately-cold-but-relevant history (e.g.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts:\n  Line 320:     // Optional empirical calibration to P(relevant). Default OFF: only applied\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-queries.ts:\n  Line 725:  * Extracts a relevant date from indexed content or path.\n","metadata":{"matches":41,"truncated":false},"title":"relevant","time":{"start":1781723341376,"end":1781723341409}},"id":"prt_ed6fca237001hQUnWXgQVZS3Gh","sessionID":"ses_12904a9e7ffe386qlv7SF1E4Vj","messageID":"msg_ed6fc39b2001IHHseFQyhQcJhe"}}
